Functional Specification Document (FSD)

Document Control
Project Name: Expense Register
Module Name: End-to-End Expense and Budget Workflow Management
Prepared By: Development Team
Reviewed By: To Be Assigned
Date: 13-Apr-2026

Revision History
Version | Date | Author | Changes
1.0 | 13-Apr-2026 | Development Team | Initial template-based FSD


Overview
Purpose
Describe the purpose of this document.
This document defines the functional behavior, user interface requirements, access controls, API expectations, and operational rules for the Expense Register application. It serves as a reference for development, QA, and business stakeholders.

Scope
Define what is included and excluded.
Included:
- Authentication and session-based login/logout
- Role-based access control across all modules
- User and department management
- Budget category management
- Budget upload (CSV/XLS/XLSX/Image OCR)
- Budget monitoring with scope restrictions
- Expense request lifecycle (create, review, approve/reject/reassign)
- Workflow setup for multi-step approvals
- Attachment upload/view/download

Excluded:
- External ERP/accounting integration
- Single Sign-On (SSO)
- Native mobile app
- Advanced analytics dashboards beyond current module views

Definitions
Term | Description
Expanse Request | Reimbursement request by an employee for an expense incurred
Expense Request | Request raised by a user for expense or purchase approval in the application
Workflow | Multi-step approval process for requests
RBAC | Role-Based Access Control enforced by role and department rules


References
BRD
- Business requirements for Expense Register process automation and control

Technical Docs
- README.md (setup, routes, module summary)
- configs/schema.sql (database structures)
- configs/env.php (environment defaults)
- controllers/, models/, libraries/ implementation references

Business Requirements
Problem Statement
Expense handling, budget visibility, and approval processes are hard to track when managed manually or in fragmented tools. This causes delays, weak auditability, and policy inconsistency.

Business Objectives
- Standardize request submission and approvals
- Enforce role and department-based control
- Improve budget governance and transparency
- Provide auditable action trails for approvals

Stakeholders
Role | Name | Responsibility
Product Owner | To Be Confirmed | Defines business priorities and acceptance criteria
Business Owner | To Be Confirmed | Approves process and policy fit
Technical Lead | To Be Confirmed | Owns architecture and implementation quality
QA Lead | To Be Confirmed | Owns validation, test coverage, and sign-off quality
Finance Team | Finance Users | Manage categories, budgets, and financial controls
HR Team | HR Users | Manage users/departments and organizational setup
Department Heads | Dept Head Users | Department-level approvals and monitoring
Employees | End Users | Raise requests and track status


User Interface / Screen Details
For each screen:

Screen Name: Login
Description: Authenticates user and starts session.
Navigation Path: ?route=auth
User Roles Allowed: Public (all users before login)
Device/Platform: Web
Responsive Behaviour: Single-column form on mobile; centered card on desktop

UI Elements
Field Name | Label | Type | Control Type | Mandatory | Read Only | Default | Placeholder | Validation | Max Length | Format | Tooltip | Remarks
username | Username | text | input | Yes | No | blank | Enter username | Required | 100 | string | User login id | Must exist in users
password | Password | password | input | Yes | No | blank | Enter password | Required | 100 | masked | Account password | Compared securely

Layout & Sections
Header: App logo/title
Footer: Copyright/footer links
Sections/Panels: Login card
Tabs/Accordions: NA
Grid/List Details: NA

Actions
Action | Description | Trigger | Pre-condition | Post-condition | API/Service Called | Success Message | Error Handling
Login | Authenticate and redirect | Click Login | Valid credentials | Session created, redirect dashboard | AuthController + AuthModel | Login successful | Invalid credentials shown

Client-side Logic
Field dependencies:
- Username and password both required
Dynamic enable/disable rules:
- Login button active only when both fields have values
Conditional visibility:
- Error banner shown only on failure

