Access Control & Security
Roles & Permissions
Role | Access Level | Screens | Actions
admin | High (policy-bound) | Dashboard, Departments, Workflows, Expenses, selected modules | View/create/edit where permitted
finance | Financial control | Budget Categories, Budget Upload, Workflows, Expenses | Manage categories, upload budgets, process workflows
hr | Organization admin | Users, Departments, Expenses | Manage users/departments, role-based visibility
manager | Department scope | Expenses, Budget Monitor (policy-based) | Review and monitor scoped data
dept_head | Department scope | Expenses, Budget Monitor (policy-based) | Department-level approvals and monitoring
employee | Limited/self scope | Expenses, Dashboard | Create and track requests

Data Security: Any conditions specifying data access logic and control
- Session-based authentication required for protected routes.
- RBAC checks enforced before controller action execution.
- Department-scoped data filtering applies for non-global roles.
- Attachment access controlled by request and authorization context.
- Sensitive database credentials are environment-configured.


API Specifications
For each API:

API Name: Login API
Endpoint: ?route=auth (controller action)
Method: POST
Description: Validate credentials and create authenticated session.

Request
Field | Type | Required | Description
username | string | Yes | Login username
password | string | Yes | Login password

Response
Field | Type | Description
success | boolean | Authentication result
message | string | Status/error message
redirect | string | Next route on success

Error Codes
Code | Message
AUTH_401 | Invalid username or password
AUTH_500 | Unexpected authentication error

------------------------------------------------------------

API Name: Create Expense Request
Endpoint: ?route=expenses/create
Method: POST
Description: Creates a new expense/purchase request and optional attachments.

Request
Field | Type | Required | Description
request_type | enum | Yes | expense/purchase/other
request_title | string | Yes | Request title
request_amount | decimal | Yes | Request amount
request_currency | string | Yes | Currency code
department_id | int | Yes | Department id
budget_category_id | int | Yes | Budget category id
workflow_id | int | Yes | Workflow id
request_priority | enum | Yes | low/medium/high
request_description | string | No | Description/details
request_notes | string | No | Additional note
attachments[] | file | No | Supporting documents

Response
Field | Type | Description
success | boolean | Creation result
message | string | Status text
request_id | int | Newly created request id
reference_no | string | Generated reference number

Error Codes
Code | Message
REQ_400 | Validation failed
REQ_403 | Unauthorized action
REQ_500 | Failed to save request


Database Design (High-Level)
- users: user identity, role slug, department mapping
- roles: role definitions and role slugs
- departments: master department details and department head
- budget_categories: category metadata for expense/purchase types
- department_budgets: budget allocation by department/period/category
- requests: request master with workflow and status
- request_actions: step-level approval/reassign trail
- request_attachments: attachment metadata and file payload
- workflows/workflow_steps: approval definitions and sequencing

Configurations
Config Key | Description | Default Value | Environment
DB_HOST | Database host | 127.0.0.1 | Local/Dev
DB_PORT | Database port | 3307 | Local/Dev
DB_NAME | Database name | expense_register | Local/Dev
DB_USER | Database user | root | Local/Dev
DB_PASS | Database password | empty | Local/Dev
APP_NAME | Application name | Expense Register | All
BASE_PATH | Base route path | /expense_portal | Web server setup dependent
CHARSET | DB charset | utf8mb4 | All


Background Jobs / Schedulers
Job Name | Frequency | Trigger | Description
Budget Import Parse | On-demand | User upload action | Parses uploaded budget files and validates rows
OCR Parse | On-demand | Image upload action | Extracts budget rows from image using OCR
Request Status Update | Event-driven | Approval/reject/reassign action | Updates current step and request status


Email / Notification Templates
Template Name: Request Submitted
Trigger Event: New request creation
Recipients: Requester (and optional reviewers)
Subject: Expense Request Submitted - {reference_no}
Body: Your request {reference_no} has been submitted and is pending review.

Variables/Placeholders
Variable | Description
{reference_no} | Request unique reference number
{request_title} | Request title
{request_amount} | Request amount
{request_status} | Current status

------------------------------------------------------------

Template Name: Request Actioned
Trigger Event: Approve/Reject/Reassign action
Recipients: Requester and relevant approvers
Subject: Expense Request {reference_no} - {action}
Body: Request {reference_no} has been {action}. Please review current status.

Variables/Placeholders
Variable | Description
{reference_no} | Request unique reference number
{action} | approve/reject/reassign
{actor_name} | Action performer
{comment} | Action comment if provided


Error Handling & Logging
Error Scenarios
Scenario | Handling | User Message
Invalid login | Reject auth and stay on login | Invalid username or password
Unauthorized route access | Redirect to forbidden page | You are not authorized for this action
Invalid request form data | Reject save and return with validation messages | Please correct highlighted fields
Invalid attachment type/size | Reject file and preserve form state | File type or size is not allowed
Database connection issue | Abort operation and show safe error feedback | Service temporarily unavailable
Budget upload row validation failure | Roll back transaction and show row errors | Upload failed due to invalid row data
Workflow configuration mismatch | Block transition and show context error | Workflow step configuration is invalid

Logging Strategy: Anything logged for developers' reference and help
- Application should log server-side exceptions with timestamps and context identifiers.
- Security-sensitive data (passwords, tokens, raw credential values) must never be logged.
- Validation and operational failures should include module/action references for troubleshooting.


Assumptions & Constraints
- Application runs in XAMPP-compatible PHP + MySQL environment.
- MySQL service must be reachable on configured host/port.
- Role and master data must be available for full module behavior.
- OCR quality depends on image quality and Tesseract installation.

Dependencies
- PHP 8.2+
- Apache web server
- MySQL/MariaDB
- Composer dependencies (PhpSpreadsheet stack)
- Tesseract OCR for image parsing


Appendix
Sample Data
- Request Type: expense
- Currency: INR
- Priority: medium
- Department: FINANCE
- Budget Category: PARKING
- Workflow: Standard Expense Approval

Additional Notes
- Route names and permissions should stay aligned with RBAC service updates.
- Any new role introduction must include policy mapping and test scenarios.
- This FSD is a functional baseline and should be versioned when business policies change.
